I’ve got the patch shape: decode fix, cheaper approval-first scanning, and a wider search radius so the PoC can actually discover an already-approved operator instead of burning gas on position reads that can never be exploited. I’m applying that now and then I’ll at least dry-run local compilation on the standalone Solidity file.
